./docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md:46:| **Logical Processor (Hyperthreading)** | System BIOS > Processor Settings | **Disabled** | Community consensus for CPU-only LLM inference: HT hurts throughput. Two logical threads competing for the same core's execution units, cache, and memory bandwidth degrades inference. You want 12 real cores per socket, not 24 virtual. With HT off, `OLLAMA_NUM_THREAD=12` maps cleanly to physical cores. |
